{{Quote|Ok, the cave and very likely your grave can be found here.|[[Watto/Legends|Watto]], to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:SD">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=class|Legacy|Squill Diving|Tatooine}}</ref>}}
The '''Squill Cave''' was a cavern located somewhere in the deserts of [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] and was home to many [[Squill (creature)|squill]] beasts.

==History==
{{Quote|I am able to watch after myself. These cold, lifeless walls do not disturb me any longer. Far too long have I lived here in solitude. I have become stoic to its effects.|A [[Unidentified Rodian hermit|hermit]], to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:TMotH">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=general|The Mark of the Hero|Tatooine}}</ref>}}
During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], a [[Unidentified Rodian hermit|Rodian hermit]] lived deep within the caves and recruited a [[Spacer/Legends|spacer]] to help him [[Quest of the Hero of Tatooine|save]] Tatoonine. This spacer would eventually become the [[Hero of Tatooine]].<ref name="SWG:TMotH" /> After the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], a [[Unidentified commoner (Anchorhead)|commoner]] in [[Anchorhead/Legends|Anchorhead]] attempted to lure spacers into going in the cave to kill some squills and collect squill hide.<ref name="SWG:ac">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=herald|a commoner|Tatooine}}</ref>

In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> a spacer also visited the cave while searching for a lost [[R2-series astromech droid/Legends|R2 unit]] diagnostic controller that was wanted by both [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Arlan Barrezz|Barrezz]] and [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Carh'la Bastra|Bastra]].<ref name="SWG:SD" />

